# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version is
#   managed by the end user. For a specific project, you may want to include these files.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1255, lock files should be placed under source control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you have platform-dependent dependencies or
#   vendor dependencies in your web-app, you might need to keep Pipfile.lock.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock should be planned to be in source control.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, pdm.lock should be planned to be in source control.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

